<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="78" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Porter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-10"><hi rend="italic">April 10,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Gresham informs Mr. Porter that the commission for the settlement of
                            claims has expiled by limitation, having disposed of twenty-five cases,
                            leaving eighteen not disposed of, and instructs him to ascertain whether
                            Chile will consent to a convention to create another commission as it is
                            earnestly desired by the United States.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>